## ⚠️ Analysis & Findings
The email was confirmed as a **phishing attempt** based on the following indicators:

- ❌ The domain `microsoftsupport.co` is **not an official Microsoft domain**
- ⚠️ The URL mimics a legitimate login page (**brand impersonation**)
- 🔗 External link redirects to a suspicious login portal
- 📧 Sender address does not match official Microsoft infrastructure

---

## 🧠 Conclusion
This incident has been classified as a **True Positive phishing attack** due to multiple clear indicators of compromise (IOCs) and domain impersonation techniques.

